mode script

// Issue #283 regression test. The linked C file references an undefined
// symbol, so the FFI shared object built by `til interpret` fails to dlopen.
// ffi_init_user_so must report this loudly at RUNTIME:
//
//   error: dlopen failed for 'tmp/ffi_<pid>.so': ...undefined symbol...
//
// Before the fix the const-folder evaluated that stderr_print at build time
// (printing a bogus "dlopen failed" while compiling the compiler) and dropped
// the call from the runtime, so a genuine load failure printed nothing here.
link_c("test/ffi_dlopen_fail.c")

til_283_boom := ext_func() returns I64 {}

println(til_283_boom().to_str())
